<br>
<br>
Not a whole lot has changed since the last patch. Some of the things that have changed, such as spellcrafting, are too new to fully realise their impact. So I will reiterate some of the points still outstanding from my previous TL report.<br>
<br>
<br>
Please make Dirty Tricks/Increased fumbles either unresistable, and/or drop the timer down to 10 minutes. Having an ability that only works every half an hour and gets resisted is silly. Its message “you throw dirt in the eyes of (target)” is also missing.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Charge:<br>
<br>
This is a great ability so far in RvR. However, it needs to have it's speed upgraded slightly to something faster than merely an endurance-free sprint. Also, it is currently switching to sprint at the end of its duration, and starts to eat up endurance. There is no animation/effect for charge currently.<br>
<br>
Flurry:<br>
<br>
There is curerent;y no annimation/effect for Flurry.<br>
<br>
Styles:<br>
<br>
Styles are the #1 complaint for Mercenaries. As stated previously on the TL boards, we have snare styles which are completely useless due to the fact that our offhand weapon will immediately break the snare.<br>
<br>
Mercenaries have no anytime chain in the Dual Wield line. Taking the level 21 style, Penumbra, and having it chain off of the level 15 style, Misty Gloom, would help to even this out.<br>
<br>
Several of our styles have heavy bleed damage.... which doesn't really add that much in the way of damage. Doubing the amount of bleed damage on heavy duration bleeds would actually make the level 50 Mercenary style something to fear.<br>
<br>
At some point in the distant past, the level 50 crush style, Devestate, was supposed to have had a stun component. Some feel that there should be some sort of long duration stun effect for a style line that is specced so high.<br>
<br>
<br>
Equipment Issues:<br>
<br>
The Long Dirk is a great boon for thrust Mercs. Thanks!<br>
<br>
Is there any way to make a shield equippable in the 2H slot? This would enable Mercenaries to be able to hot-key a shield for engage. At this moment in time, a lot of backpack juggling has to occur before we can accomplish this.<br>
<br>
<br>
Realm Abilities: <br>
<br>
Prevent Flight -- if this were lowered to cost 10 points, it is likely that more Mercenaries would purchase it. That's a lot of RSPS to shell out for a 35% chance to snare.<br>
<br>
Void has basically been superceded by Flurry. I don't know of a single Mercenary that has this realm ability. Please scrap it and give us something else. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
